itch于1435年出生在英国艾可維丁頓时，他的父亲William Fitch25岁，母亲Joanna Goldsborough25岁。他于1460年与Juliana Marston在英国艾可維丁頓结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。他去世于1468年4月9日在英国英格兰艾可維丁頓享年33岁，埋葬在英国英格兰艾可維丁頓。"},"hr":{"1435–9 April 1468":"1435.–9. travnja 1468.","1435–1468":"1435.–1468","1447–1474":"1447–1474","1435–1514":"1435.–1514","–1475":"–1475","1465–1514":"1465.–1514","1410–1466":"1410–1466","1410–1453":"1410–1453.","24 April 1466":"24. travnja 1466.","1460":"1460.","18 April 1468":"18. travnja 1468.","1514":"1514","1447":"1447","1435":"1435.","9 April 1468":"9. travnja 1468.","1468":"1468","1455":"1455","1466":"1466","1465":"1465.","1410":"1410","1453":"1453.","about 1435":"oko 1435.","1475":"1475","1474":"1474","about 1465":"oko 1465.","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Wicken, Essex, England":"Essex, Engleska, United Kingdom","Widdington, Essex, England":"Widdington, Essex, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1435–9 April 1468":"1435–9. dubna 1468","1435–1468":"1435–1468","1447–1474":"1447–1474","1435–1514":"1435–1514","–1475":"–1475","1465–1514":"1465–1514","1410–1466":"1410–1466","1410–1453":"1410–1453","24 April 1466":"24. dubna 1466","1460":"1460","18 April 1468":"18. dubna 1468","1514":"1514","1447":"1447","1435":"1435","9 April 1468":"9. dubna 1468","1468":"1468","1455":"1455","1466":"1466","1465":"1465","1410":"1410","1453":"1453","about 1435":"okolo 1435","1475":"1475","1474":"1474","about 1465":"okolo 1465","Essex, England":"Essex, Anglie","Wicken, Essex, England":"Essex, Anglie, United Kingdom","Widdington, Essex, England":"Widdington, Essex, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1435–9 April 1468":"1435–9. april 1468","1435–1468":"1435–1468","1447–1474":"1447–1474","1435–1514":"1435–1514","–1475":"–1475","1465–1514":"1465–1514","1410–1466":"1410–1466","1410–1453":"1410–1453","24 April 1466":"24. april 1466","1460":"1460","18 April 1468":"18. april 1468","1514":"1514","1447":"1447","1435":"1435","9 April 1468":"9. april 1468","1468":"1468","1455":"1455","1466":"1466","1465":"1465","1410":"1410","1453":"1453","about 1435":"omkring 1435","1475":"1475","1474":"1474","about 1465":"omkring 1465","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Wicken, Essex, England":"Essex, England, United Kingdom","Widdington, Essex, England":"Widdington, Essex, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1435–9 April 1468":"1435–9 april 1468","1435–1468":"1435–1468","1447–1474":"1447–1474","1435–1514":"1435–1514","–1475":"–1475","1465–1514":"1465–1514","1410–1466":"1410–1466","1410–1453":"1410–1453","24 April 1466":"24 april 1466","1460":"1460","18 April 1468":"18 april 1468","1514":"1514","1447":"1447","1435":"1435","9 April 1468":"9 april 1468","1468":"1468","1455":"1455","1466":"1466","1465":"1465","1410":"1410","1453":"1453","about 1435":"circa 1435","1475":"1475","1474":"1474","about 1465":"circa 1465","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Wicken, Essex, England":"Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Widdington, Essex, England":"Widdington, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1435–9 April 1468":"1435–9 April 1468","1435–1468":"1435–1468","1447–1474":"1447–1474","1435–1514":"1435–1514","–1475":"–1475","1465–1514":"1465–1514","1410–1466":"1410–1466","1410–1453":"1410–1453","24 April 1466":"24 April 1466","1460":"1460","18 April 1468":"18 April 1468","1514":"1514","1447":"1447","1435":"1435","9 April 1468":"9 April 1468","1468":"1468","1455":"1455","1466":"1466","1465":"1465","1410":"1410","1453":"1453","about 1435":"about 1435","1475":"1475","1474":"1474","about 1465":"about 1465","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Wicken, Essex, England":"Essex, England, United Kingdom","Widdington, Essex, England":"Widdington, Essex, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fitch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from Old French <i>fiche</i>, perhaps ‘pointed implement for fixing or transfixing something or someone’ (such as a lance?), a derivative of Old French <i>fichier</i> ‘to fix, fasten, pin on, stick into, pierce’. Compare Modern French <i>fiche</i> ‘peg, pin’. Reaney remarks that ‘as Hugh <i>Malet</i> is said to have abandoned for a time his nickname ‘little hammer’ in favor of <i>Fichet</i> (see   Mallet  ), <i>fiche</i> must have been used of a pointed weapon, a spear or lance, and <i>Fitch</i> and <i>Fitchett</i> (see   Fitchett  ) of a spearman or a knight famous for his exploits with the lance’. Use of <i>Fiche</i> as a personal name is possibly implied by diminutive personal name forms such as <i>Fechet</i> (see   Fitchett  ) and <i>Fechel</i>, attested in <i>Fechel</i> de Fercalahn, 1225–50. The latter is perhaps the source of the now extinct English surname <b>Fetchell</b>.","occasionally a variant of   Fitz  .","English:"],"variants":[{"name":"Fitchett","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from Old French <i>Fichet</i>, <i>Fichot</i>, or (in northern France) <i>Fiket</i>, <i>Fikot</i>, diminutive forms of <i>fiche</i> or <i>fike</i> ‘pointed implement for fixing or transfixing something or someone’ (such as a spear?), used as a nickname and as a personal name. See   Fitch  ."]},{"name":"Mallet","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Jean-Yves, Adelard, Alain, Henri, Jacques, Leonce, Lucien, Monique, Philippe.","French: nickname from a diminutive of   Mal   ‘bad’. Alternatively, from a derivative of the related Old French word <i>maleit</i> ‘accursed’ (from Latin <i>maledictus</i>, the opposite of <i>benedictus</i> ‘blessed’), applied as a nickname for an unlucky person. Compare   Malet   1.","French: variant of   Malet   2, an Old French pet form of the personal name   Malo  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":20,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Fitch was born in 1435, in Widdington, Essex, England, his father, William Fitch, was 25 and his mother, Joanna Goldsborough, was 25. He married Juliana Marston in 1460, in Widdington, Essex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 9 April 1468, in Widdington, Essex, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 33, and was buried in Widdington, Essex, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1435–9 April 1468":"1435–9. aprill 1468","1435–1468":"1435–1468","1447–1474":"1447–1474","1435–1514":"1435–1514","–1475":"–1475","1465–1514":"1465–1514","1410–1466":"1410–1466","1410–1453":"1410–1453","24 April 1466":"24. aprill 1466","1460":"1460","18 April 1468":"18. aprill 1468","1514":"1514","1447":"1447","1435":"1435","9 April 1468":"9. aprill 1468","1468":"1468","1455":"1455","1466":"1466","1465":"1465","1410":"1410","1453":"1453","about 1435":"umbes 1435","1475":"1475","1474":"1474","about 1465":"umbes 1465","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Wicken, Essex, England":"Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Widdington, Essex, England":"Widdington, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1435–9 April 1468":"1435–9. huhtikuuta 1468","1435–1468":"1435–1468","1447–1474":"1447–1474","1435–1514":"1435–1514","–1475":"–1475","1465–1514":"1465–1514","1410–1466":"1410–1466","1410–1453":"1410–1453","24 April 1466":"24. huhtikuuta 1466","1460":"1460","18 April 1468":"18. huhtikuuta 1468","1514":"1514","1447":